{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BsTeG6DW88qcuYbWQWrptw","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Implementation History — 305-peek-operations-admin\n2\t\n3\tIteration log for the autonomous spec loop. Each entry records what was\n4\tattempted and whether it succeeded. The agent reads this file at the start\n5\tof every iteration to understand prior context.\n6\t\n7\t---\n8\t\n9\t## Iteration 1 — 2026-04-25\n10\t\n11\t- Added `jose@6.2.2` to `peek/package.json` as a runtime dep.\n12\t- Rewrote `peek/src/server/cloudflare-access.ts` on top of `jose`:\n13\t  `jwtVerify` with `algorithms: ['RS256']`, `audience`, `issuer`, and\n14\t  `currentDate`, using `createLocalJWKSet` when callers pass an in-memory\n15\t  JWKS (test path) and `createRemoteJWKSet` against\n16\t  `${teamDomain}/cdn-cgi/access/certs` otherwise (cached per issuer).\n17\t- Removed all custom RSA/JWKS/base64url/JSON-claim crypto helpers; mapped\n18\t  jose error subclasses (`JWTExpired`, `JWTClaimValidationFailed` with\n19\t  `claim === \"iss\"`/`\"aud\"`, `JOSEAlgNotAllowed`, `JOSENotSupported`,\n20\t  `JWKSNoMatchingKey`, `JWSSignatureVerificationFailed`,\n21\t  `JWKSTimeout`/`JWKSInvalid`/`JWKInvalid`, `JWTInvalid`/`JWSInvalid`)\n22\t  back onto the existing `CloudflareAccessVerificationReason` union so\n23\t  callers and existing tests are unchanged.\n24\t- Preserved the public surface: `verifyCloudflareAccessJwt`,\n25\t  `getVerifiedCloudflareAccessEmailFromHeaders`, and\n26\t  `VERIFIED_ACCESS_EMAIL_HEADER` keep their shapes; `proxy.ts` and\n27\t  `app/layout.tsx` need no edits.\n28\t- Targeted check: `pnpm --dir peek lint`, `pnpm --dir peek typecheck`,\n29\t  and `pnpm --dir peek test` — all green; 21/21 unit tests pass.\n30\t\n31\t## Iteration 1 — 2026-04-25T09:45:06Z — BLOCKED\n32\t- **Blocker**: No file changes detected — agent made no progress.\n33\t- **Log**: iteration-001.log\n34\t\n35\t## Iteration 2 — 2026-04-25\n36\t\n37\t- Expanded `peek/src/server/__tests__/cloudflare-access.test.ts` for the\n38\t  jose-backed verifier: malformed token, expired (`exp` in the past),\n39\t  invalid issuer (signed with `https://other.cloudflareaccess.com`),\n40\t  invalid audience, bad signature (sign with key A, present JWK B with\n41\t  the same `kid`), `alg: \"none\"` rejection, missing email claim\n42\t  (returns `ok: true, email: null`), and case/whitespace normalization\n43\t  (`\"  Admin@Example.COM  \"` → `\"admin@example.com\"`).\n44\t- Lowercased + trimmed in `normalizeEmail` so the verified email\n45\t  identity is canonical for FR-2 role matching.\n46\t- Replaced the implicit `NODE_ENV === \"development\"` bypass in\n47\t  `peek/proxy.ts` with the spec-required explicit `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL`\n48\t  bypass: dev-only, validates email shape, sets the\n49\t  `VERIFIED_ACCESS_EMAIL_HEADER` so server context still gets a normalized\n50\t  actor identity. Production never honors the bypass; missing CF env in\n51\t  prod still returns 500.\n52\t- Rewrote `peek/src/server/__tests__/cloudflare-access-middleware.test.ts`\n53\t  with `vi.stubEnv` (TS forbids assigning to `process.env.NODE_ENV`) and\n54\t  added: prod blocks without JWT (existing), prod 500 on missing CF env,\n55\t  prod ignores `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL`, dev honors `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL`\n56\t  with case normalization, dev rejects malformed `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL`.\n57\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n58\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (31/31, +10 new).\n59\t\n60\t## Iteration 2 — 2026-04-25T10:32:41Z — OK\n61\t- **Log**: iteration-002.log\n62\t\n63\t## Iteration 3 — 2026-04-25\n64\t\n65\t- Added `peek/src/server/access-policy.ts`:\n66\t  - `PeekRole = \"business\" | \"admin\"`, `PeekRolePolicyEntry = { match, role }`\n67\t    where `match` is either an exact email (`alice@example.com`) or a wildcard\n68\t    domain (`*@example.com`).\n69\t  - `parsePeekRolePolicy(raw)` validates entries: trims/lowercases, drops\n70\t    invalid `role` values, drops missing/non-string `match` values, validates\n71\t    wildcard domain shape, and de-duplicates exact `(match, role)` pairs.\n72\t  - `loadPeekRolePolicyFromEnv()` reads `PEEK_ACCESS_POLICY` JSON; returns\n73\t    `[]` on missing/malformed input (fail-closed for env-driven config).\n74\t  - `normalizeActorEmail()` and `resolveRoleForEmail()` implement\n75\t    case-insensitive matching and admin precedence: any matching `admin`\n76\t    rule wins (short-circuit), otherwise first matching `business` wins.\n77\t  - `getPeekActorContext()` reads `next/headers` for the trusted\n78\t    `VERIFIED_ACCESS_EMAIL_HEADER` (set only by the proxy), normalizes it,\n79\t    resolves the role, and returns `{ email, role }` or `null`. Browser\n80\t    headers are never trusted — the policy is loaded from server env only.\n81\t- Hardened `peek/proxy.ts`: clones `request.headers` and unconditionally\n82\t  `delete()`s `VERIFIED_ACCESS_EMAIL_HEADER` at the top of every code path,\n83\t  so a spoofed `x-peek-verified-access-email` header from the browser cannot\n84\t  survive into server context — even on the dev no-config and dev no-bypass\n85\t  branches. The header is only ever (re-)set with the dev-bypass email or a\n86\t  jose-verified Cloudflare Access email.\n87\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n88\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (31/31, no regressions; access-policy unit tests land in\n89\t  the next iteration per the checklist split).\n90\t\n91\t## Iteration 3 — 2026-04-25T10:36:33Z — OK\n92\t- **Log**: iteration-003.log\n93\t\n94\t## Iteration 4 — 2026-04-25\n95\t\n96\t- Extended `peek/src/server/access-policy.ts` with the FR-2 centralized\n97\t  route-prefix and action-id authorization helpers:\n98\t  - `PEEK_ROUTE_RULES` table (`/audit` → `admin`); other routes fall back to\n99\t    `PEEK_DEFAULT_ROUTE_ROLES = [\"business\", \"admin\"]` per System Invariant\n100\t    #6 (read-only default for any resolved peek role).\n101\t  - `PEEK_ACTION_RULES` table covering the FR-14 initial mutation candidates:\n102\t    `kol_rate.update` (`business`/`admin`), `fraud_flag.status.update`\n103\t    (`admin`), `dogpile.cancel` (`admin`), `reward_config.update` (`admin`).\n104\t  - `getRequiredRolesForRoute(path)` normalizes the path (strips query/hash,\n105\t    trailing slash) and resolves the most-specific matching prefix; unknown\n106\t    paths return the documented default.\n107\t  - `isRouteAllowedForRole(path, role)` → false for `null` role, otherwise\n108\t    membership in the resolved required-roles list.\n109\t  - `getRequiredRolesForAction(actionId)` returns the required roles or\n110\t    `null` when the action id is unknown; `isActionAllowedForRole` fails\n111\t    closed (returns false) on unknown action ids or `null` role.\n112\t  - All rule tables and helpers accept overridable rule arrays so the test\n113\t    suite (next iteration) can exercise unit-table edge cases without\n114\t    coupling to the live policy.\n115\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n116\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (31/31, no regressions; new helpers will get dedicated\n117\t  unit coverage in the next iteration per the checklist split).\n118\t\n119\t## Iteration 4 — 2026-04-25T10:39:30Z — OK\n120\t- **Log**: iteration-004.log\n121\t\n122\t## Iteration 5 — 2026-04-25\n123\t\n124\t- Added `peek/src/server/__tests__/access-policy.test.ts` (44 tests) covering\n125\t  the FR-2 surface end-to-end:\n126\t  - `parsePeekRolePolicy`: non-array input, trim+lowercase normalization,\n127\t    invalid roles dropped, missing/non-string `match` dropped, malformed\n128\t    wildcard domains dropped (including `*@`, `*@*.com`, `*@with space.com`),\n129\t    malformed exact emails dropped, exact `(match, role)` de-duplication\n130\t    that still preserves distinct roles for the same email, and rejection of\n131\t    non-object array items.\n132\t  - `loadPeekRolePolicyFromEnv`: empty env, malformed JSON, valid env policy\n133\t    (using `vi.stubEnv(\"PEEK_ACCESS_POLICY\", …)`).\n134\t  - `normalizeActorEmail`: trim+lowercase, nullish/empty/invalid → null.\n135\t  - `resolveRoleForEmail`: invalid email, exact match (case-insensitive),\n136\t    wildcard domain match, admin precedence both ways (exact admin beats\n137\t    wildcard business; wildcard admin beats exact business), no match, and\n138\t    empty policy.\n139\t  - Route helpers: `getRequiredRolesForRoute` returns the documented default\n140\t    for unknown routes (`/`, `/users`, `/games/flipyou`), `admin` for `/audit`\n141\t    + subpaths, refuses prefix-substring leakage (`/auditing` → default), strips\n142\t    `?query` and `#hash`, normalizes paths missing a leading slash, and picks\n143\t    the most specific matching prefix when multiple rules match.\n144\t  - `isRouteAllowedForRole`: denies on null/undefined role, allows\n145\t    business+admin on default routes, denies business on `/audit` while\n146\t    allowing admin.\n147\t  - Action helpers: `getRequiredRolesForAction` returns roles for every FR-14\n148\t    initial mutation id and `null` for unknown ids; `isActionAllowedForRole`\n149\t    fails closed on unknown ids and null role, admin can perform every initial\n150\t    mutation, business can do `kol_rate.update` only, and an injected rules\n151\t    array overrides without leaking the live table.\n152\t  - `getPeekActorContext` (with `vi.mock(\"next/headers\")`): missing header →\n153\t    null, no policy match → null, empty policy → null, exact admin match →\n154\t    `{ email, role: \"admin\" }`, wildcard match with case+whitespace\n155\t    normalization, malformed verified email header → null.\n156\t  - Live tables: asserts `/audit` rule is admin-only and that\n157\t    `PEEK_ACTION_RULES` includes the FR-14 initial mutation ids.\n158\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n159\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (75/75 — was 31/31, +44 new).\n160\t\n161\t## Iteration 5 — 2026-04-25T10:42:46Z — OK\n162\t- **Log**: iteration-005.log\n163\t\n164\t## Iteration 6 — 2026-04-25\n165\t\n166\t- Added `peek/src/lib/access-policy.ts` exposing the browser-safe `PeekRole`\n167\t  literal + `PEEK_ROLES` list + `isPeekRole` guard. Server-only policy details\n168\t  (env loading, route + action rules, actor context, `next/headers` reads) stay\n169\t  in `peek/src/server/access-policy.ts`; the server module now re-exports\n170\t  `PeekRole` from the lib module so existing callers/tests are unchanged.\n171\t- Extended `peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts` with foundational FR-4 view-model\n172\t  primitives, all browser-safe (no server imports, fully serializable):\n173\t  - `PeekActorView` — `{ email, role }` for the admin shell badge.\n174\t  - `PeekMetric` — stable id, label, value, valueDisplay, unit, source,\n175\t    windowLabel, asOf, definition, freshness, drilldownHref. `PeekMetricFreshness`\n176\t    union covers `live | cached | manual | sampled` so pages can declare how\n177\t    fresh the data is per FR-4.\n178\t  - `PeekPagination` — `{ page, pageSize, totalCount, totalPages }`.\n179\t  - `PeekTableSort` + `PeekSortDirection` for URL-addressable sort state.\n180\t  - `PeekTableFilter` + `PeekFilterKind` (`text | select | boolean | date |\n181\t    dateRange`) + `PeekFilterOption` for the URL-addressable filter primitive.\n182\t  - `PeekStatusTone` (`neutral | positive | warning | negative | info`) for the\n183\t    shared status-chip component.\n184\t  - `PeekEmptyState` for the operator-copy empty-state primitive.\n185\t  - `PeekTableColumn` (id/label/align/sortable), `PeekTableRowBase`\n186\t    (`{ id, href }`) which per-feature row types extend, and a generic\n187\t    `PeekTableViewModel<TRow>` envelope (columns, rows, pagination, filters,\n188\t    sort, empty) used by feature pages.\n189\t- Existing 303-era `PeekSummary`, `PeekUserRow`, and `PeekUserDetail` shapes\n190\t  remain unchanged; per-feature view models for users/referrals/games/queue/\n191\t  audit/exports get added inside their respective feature iterations.\n192\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n193\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (75/75, no regressions).\n194\t\n195\t\n196\t## Iteration 6 — 2026-04-25T10:46:50Z — OK\n197\t- **Log**: iteration-006.log\n198\t\n199\t## Iteration 7 — 2026-04-25\n200\t\n201\t- Extended `peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts` with the foundational FR-11 audit and\n202\t  FR-12 export contracts (browser-safe, fully serializable, no server imports):\n203\t  - `PeekAuditEventType` union: `peek.search`, `peek.user.view_sensitive`,\n204\t    `peek.export`, `peek.access.denied`, `peek.change.applied`,\n205\t    `peek.change.rejected` — paired with `PEEK_AUDIT_EVENT_TYPES` const list +\n206\t    `isPeekAuditEventType` guard for parsing rows back from `operator_events`.\n207\t  - `PEEK_AUDIT_REDACTED = \"[REDACTED]\"` sentinel for the writer to substitute\n208\t    in place of any redacted value before persisting; the audit-view UI will\n209\t    render the token verbatim so reviewers see that a field was redacted (not\n210\t    silently absent), per FR-11 (no JWTs, access tokens, DB URLs, private keys,\n211\t    or raw secrets in payload).\n212\t  - `PeekAuditScalar`, `PeekAuditChange { field, before, after }`, and\n213\t    `PeekAuditPayload` capturing every FR-11 field: `actorEmail`, `route`,\n214\t    `actionId`, `resourceType`, `resourceId`, `filterSummary`, `resultCount`,\n215\t    `requestId`, `rejectionReason`, `changes` (mutation before/after diff).\n216\t  - `PeekAuditEvent { id, eventType, createdAt, payload }` view model for the\n217\t    audit page table.\n218\t  - `PEEK_EXPORT_ROW_CAP_DEFAULT = 5000` baseline cap; `PeekExportEntity` union\n219\t    enumerating the entities expected to ship CSV exports (users, referrers,\n220\t    KOL, claims, rounds, transactions, queue, audit).\n221\t  - `PeekExportRow = Record<string, string>` keyed by table column id so export\n222\t    rows track the rendered table view-model fields (FR-12 row-mapping rule).\n223\t  - `PeekExportFilenameInput { entity, date, filterSlug }` and\n224\t    `PeekExportResult { filename, rowCount, rowCap, rowCapApplied, columns,\n225\t    rows }` so the export helper (later iteration) can return both the bounded\n226\t    rows and a cap-applied indicator the UI surfaces to the operator.\n227\t- Per-feature view models (queue payload redaction, audit filter view models,\n228\t  per-entity export row aliases) get added inside their respective feature\n229\t  iterations.\n230\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n231\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (75/75, no regressions).\n232\t\n233\t## Iteration 7 — 2026-04-25T10:50:01Z — OK\n234\t- **Log**: iteration-007.log\n235\t\n236\t## Iteration 8 — 2026-04-25\n237\t\n238\t- Added foundational FR-3/FR-4 UI primitives part A (dense table, metric strip,\n239\t  filter bar) — all server-component-friendly (no client state), browser-safe\n240\t  imports only:\n241\t  - `peek/src/components/peek-table.tsx` — generic `PeekTable<TRow>` rendering a\n242\t    `PeekTableViewModel<TRow>`. Sortable column headers render `next/link`\n243\t    anchors using a caller-supplied `buildSortHref(columnId, nextDirection)`\n244\t    callback (component computes the toggle: currently-sorted desc → asc, else\n245\t    desc); active-sort header carries a `▲`/`▼` indicator and `aria-sort`. Cells\n246\t    are rendered via a typed `renderCell(row, columnId)` callback so per-feature\n247\t    row shapes stay strongly typed without leaking into the table component.\n248\t    Empty rows render the view-model's `empty` operator copy (`role=\"status\"`),\n249\t    and a non-null `error` prop renders `role=\"alert\"` instead of the table.\n250\t  - `peek/src/components/metric-strip.tsx` — renders a `ReadonlyArray<PeekMetric>`\n251\t    grid of cards with the FR-4 bookkeeping visible (label, valueDisplay + unit,\n252\t    definition, source, windowLabel, as-of, freshness chip, optional drill-down\n253\t    `Link`). Empty array renders an operator status; non-null error renders an\n254\t    alert instead of the grid.\n255\t  - `peek/src/components/filter-bar.tsx` — `<form method=\"get\">` with `name=`\n256\t    inputs matching each filter id so applied filters round-trip through the\n257\t    URL. Supports `text` / `select` / `boolean` / `date` / `dateRange` (the last\n258\t    splits on `..` and emits `${id}From` and `${id}To` named inputs). Required\n259\t    filters get a `*` suffix; non-required `select` filters get an empty/Any\n260\t    leading option. Empty filter list renders an operator status; non-null error\n261\t    renders an alert.\n262\t- Added component tests covering populated / sparse / error for each:\n263\t  - `peek-table.test.tsx` (3 tests): populated renders columns, rows via\n264\t    renderCell, toggling sort hrefs (active desc → asc next), `aria-sort`\n265\t    descending on the active column, and `▼` indicator; sparse renders\n266\t    `role=\"status\"` with the empty-state copy and no `<table>`; error renders\n267\t    `role=\"alert\"` and suppresses both the table and the empty state.\n268\t  - `metric-strip.test.tsx` (4 tests): populated renders label/value/unit/\n269\t    definition/source/window/asOf/freshness/drilldown link; sparse-data variant\n270\t    (null asOf, null drilldownHref) renders a `—` and no link; empty array\n271\t    renders operator status; error renders alert.\n272\t  - `filter-bar.test.tsx` (3 tests): populated renders all five filter kinds\n273\t    with default values, the `windowFrom` / `windowTo` split inputs, and the\n274\t    submit button; empty list renders operator status; error renders alert and\n275\t    no `role=\"search\"` form.\n276\t- No changes to existing 303-era components (`SummaryStrip`, `UsersTable`,\n277\t  `PaginationControls`) — those stay as feature-specific surfaces; the new\n278\t  primitives become the default for FR-3/FR-4 feature pages going forward.\n279\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n280\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (85/85 — was 75/75, +10 new across 3 new component test files).\n281\t\n282\t## Iteration 8 — 2026-04-25T10:55:00Z — OK\n283\t- **Log**: iteration-008.log\n284\t\n285\t## Iteration 8 — 2026-04-25T10:55:14Z — OK\n286\t- **Log**: iteration-008.log\n287\t\n288\t## Iteration 9 — 2026-04-25\n289\t\n290\t- Added foundational FR-3/FR-4 UI primitives part B (state primitives) — all\n291\t  server-component-friendly (no client state), browser-safe imports only:\n292\t  - `peek/src/components/status-chip.tsx` — renders a `PeekStatusTone`-toned\n293\t    chip via `<span role=\"status\" data-tone={tone}>`. Default tone is\n294\t    `neutral`; `null`/empty label collapses to a `—` placeholder span with\n295\t    `aria-label=\"status missing\"`; non-null `error` prop renders `role=\"alert\"`\n296\t    instead of the chip. Tones (`neutral | positive | warning | negative |\n297\t    info`) drive the background/foreground/border palette so per-feature\n298\t    status surfaces (claim status, queue state, round phase, fraud flag) get\n299\t    a consistent operator-readable chip.\n300\t  - `peek/src/components/empty-state.tsx` — renders a `PeekEmptyState`\n301\t    `{ title, body }` inside `role=\"status\"` for operator-copy empties (FR-3\n302\t    \"Empty states explain the absence of data in operator terms\"). `body` is\n303\t    nullable; non-null `error` renders `role=\"alert\"` instead.\n304\t  - `peek/src/components/detail-panel.tsx` — renders a\n305\t    `ReadonlyArray<PeekDetailSection>` (`{ id, label, body: ReactNode }`) as\n306\t    `<nav aria-label>` anchor links + a stack of `<section id={id}\n307\t    aria-labelledby>` blocks with `<h2>` headings. `activeId` toggles\n308\t    `aria-current=\"true\"` + a highlighted style on the active link; empty\n309\t    sections list renders an operator empty state; non-null `error` renders\n310\t    `role=\"alert\"`. Body is `ReactNode` (not a serializable view-model field),\n311\t    so the detail-section type lives in the component module rather than the\n312\t    browser-safe types module.\n313\t- Added component tests covering populated / sparse / error for each:\n314\t  - `status-chip.test.tsx` (4 tests): populated renders label + `data-tone`\n315\t    + forwards `title`; populated default-tone falls back to `neutral`; sparse\n316\t    `label={null}` renders `—` with `aria-label=\"status missing\"` and no\n317\t    `data-tone`; error renders `role=\"alert\"` and suppresses the chip.\n318\t  - `empty-state.test.tsx` (3 tests): populated renders title + body inside\n319\t    `role=\"status\"`; sparse `body=null` renders only the title (single `<p>`);\n320\t    error renders `role=\"alert\"` and suppresses the status region.\n321\t  - `detail-panel.test.tsx` (4 tests): populated renders nav links in section\n322\t    order with correct `href=\"#…\"` anchors, marks `activeId=\"linked-accounts\"`\n323\t    via `aria-current=\"true\"`, and renders each section's body + `<h2>`\n324\t    heading; populated without `activeId` leaves every link non-active;\n325\t    sparse renders the operator empty state with title + body and no nav;\n326\t    error renders `role=\"alert\"` and suppresses both nav and status.\n327\t- Existing 303-era components (`SummaryStrip`, `UsersTable`,\n328\t  `PaginationControls`, `UserDetailCard`) and the iteration-8 layout/data\n329\t  primitives (`PeekTable`, `MetricStrip`, `FilterBar`) are untouched — the\n330\t  state primitives complete the FR-3/FR-4 foundational set used by upcoming\n331\t  feature pages.\n332\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n333\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (96/96 — was 85/85, +11 new across 3 new component test\n334\t  files).\n335\t\n336\t## Iteration 9 — 2026-04-25T10:58:00Z — OK\n337\t- **Log**: iteration-009.log\n338\t\n339\t## Iteration 9 — 2026-04-25T10:58:58Z — OK\n340\t- **Log**: iteration-009.log\n341\t\n342\t## Iteration 10 — 2026-04-25\n343\t\n344\t- Added the FR-3 persistent admin shell — a server-rendered chrome that wraps\n345\t  every peek route and resolves the verified Cloudflare Access actor against\n346\t  the FR-2 local role policy:\n347\t  - `peek/src/components/admin-shell.tsx` — pure presentational\n348\t    server-component-friendly shell. Takes `actor: PeekActorView | null`,\n349\t    `navItems: ReadonlyArray<AdminShellNavItem>`, optional `accessIssue:\n350\t    \"no-identity\" | \"no-role\"`, and `children`. Renders `aria-label=\"Peek\n351\t    admin shell\"` header with brand, primary navigation (`<nav\n352\t    aria-label=\"Primary\">`), and an actor-identity strip with a tone-coded\n353\t    role badge (`data-role`, `aria-label=\"Resolved role: ...\"`). When\n354\t    `accessIssue` is set, the shell suppresses nav, identity, and `children`,\n355\t    and renders an `aria-label=\"Access denied\"` `role=\"alert\"` block with a\n356\t    generic operator-readable title + body — never echoing the verified email\n357\t    so the missing-config / no-identity branches do not leak sensitive data.\n358\t  - `peek/src/server/admin-shell-nav.ts` — server-only nav model. Declares\n359\t    `PEEK_ADMIN_SHELL_NAV` covering the FR-3 groups (Users, Growth, Games,\n360\t    Economy, Operations, Audit, Access) and `getVisibleNavItemsForRole(role)`\n361\t    which filters via `isRouteAllowedForRole` (so `/audit` is admin-only and\n362\t    null roles see nothing), keeping page authorization centralized in the\n363\t    FR-2 policy module.\n364\t  - `peek/app/layout.tsx` — replaced the ad-hoc header with `AdminShell`.\n365\t    Reads the trusted `VERIFIED_ACCESS_EMAIL_HEADER` and `getPeekActorContext`\n366\t    once per request, classifies the access state (`no-identity` when the\n367\t    proxy did not set the verified email; `no-role` when an email is present\n368\t    but no role resolves), and passes the role-filtered nav into the shell so\n369\t    inaccessible routes never appear in the link list.\n370\t- Added shell coverage:\n371\t  - `src/components/__tests__/admin-shell.test.tsx` (6 tests): admin sees\n372\t    every nav group + email + admin-toned badge; business-style filtered nav\n373\t    omits Audit; `accessIssue=\"no-role\"` renders the alert and suppresses\n374\t    nav/identity/children with no `@` characters in the alert text;\n375\t    `accessIssue=\"no-identity\"` renders the generic missing-identity alert\n376\t    with the same suppression; stale-actor + access-issue still hides the\n377\t    email; empty navItems renders identity but no nav.\n378\t  - `src/server/__tests__/admin-shell-nav.test.ts` (4 tests): admin → all\n379\t    7 groups; business → 6 groups (Audit hidden); null role → empty list;\n380\t    declared nav covers the FR-3 group ids in order.\n381\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n382\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (106/106 — was 96/96, +10 new across 2 new test files;\n383\t  the existing layout was the only modified surface and its consumers\n384\t  (`app/page.tsx`, `app/users/[userId]/page.tsx`) keep their `<main>`\n385\t  wrappers because the shell renders only chrome, not a `<main>` element).\n386\t\n387\t## Iteration 10 — 2026-04-25 — OK\n388\t\n389\t## Iteration 10 — 2026-04-25T11:05:34Z — OK\n390\t- **Log**: iteration-010.log\n391\t\n392\t## Iteration 11 — 2026-04-25\n393\t\n394\t- Added the FR-11 audit writer module under `peek/src/server/audit/**` so\n395\t  `peek.*` operator events land in the existing `operator_events` table\n396\t  without a new migration:\n397\t  - `peek/src/server/audit/redact.ts` — `looksLikeSecret`, `redactScalar`,\n398\t    `redactNullableString`, `redactChange`, and `redactPayload`. Patterns\n399\t    cover JWTs (`eyJ…\\.…\\.…`), DB connection URLs (postgres/mysql/mongodb/\n400\t    redis/amqp), `-----BEGIN […] PRIVATE KEY-----` blocks, `Bearer …`\n401\t    headers, and `cf-access-jwt-assertion: …` lines. Matches are replaced\n402\t    with `PEEK_AUDIT_REDACTED` from `peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts`. Mutation\n403\t    `changes[]` entries get the same scalar redaction so before/after\n404\t    string values cannot persist secrets.\n405\t  - `peek/src/server/audit/writer.ts` — `writePeekAuditEvent({ eventType,\n406\t    payload }, options)` that runs every payload through `redactPayload`,\n407\t    inserts into `operator_events (event_type, payload)` (pda left null —\n408\t    peek records are not round-keyed), and returns\n409\t    `{ ok: true } | { ok: false, reason: \"invalid_payload\" | \"insert_failed\" }`.\n410\t    Empty `actorEmail` short-circuits to `invalid_payload` so unauthenticated\n411\t    paths never write a row. DB errors are caught and only forwarded to a\n412\t    server-side `logger` (defaults to `console.error`); the error detail\n413\t    never reaches the writer's return value, so callers cannot accidentally\n414\t    leak DB internals to the browser.\n415\t  - `peek/src/server/audit/index.ts` — public re-exports\n416\t    (`writePeekAuditEvent`, the result types, and the redaction helpers).\n417\t  - The writer accepts an injectable `Sql` and `logger` so the next\n418\t    iteration's tests can drive it without touching live Postgres.\n419\t- Inserts use `sql.json(...)` to keep the JSONB serialization consistent\n420\t  with the backend's existing `operator_events` writer pattern in\n421\t  `backend/src/db/rounds.ts`.\n422\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n423\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (106/106, no regressions; audit-writer tests land in the\n424\t  next iteration per the checklist split).\n425\t\n426\t## Iteration 11 — 2026-04-25T11:10:28Z — OK\n427\t- **Log**: iteration-011.log\n428\t\n429\t## Iteration 12 — 2026-04-25\n430\t\n431\t- Added `peek/src/server/audit/__tests__/writer.test.ts` (9 tests) covering the\n432\t  FR-11 audit-writer surface end-to-end:\n433\t  - **Sensitive read**: `peek.user.view_sensitive` insert carries the full\n434\t    payload (route, actionId, resourceType/Id, filterSummary, resultCount,\n435\t    requestId) verbatim into `operator_events`; SQL string contains\n436\t    `insert into operator_events`.\n437\t  - **Export**: `peek.export` insert carries actionId, resultCount, and\n438\t    filterSummary unchanged.\n439\t  - **Access denial**: `peek.access.denied` insert carries route + a\n440\t    `rejectionReason` (e.g. `role_required:admin`) without leaking secrets.\n441\t  - **Mutation applied**: `peek.change.applied` insert carries the\n442\t    `changes[]` before/after array with mixed scalar types (number + string)\n443\t    intact.\n444\t  - **Mutation rejected**: `peek.change.rejected` insert carries\n445\t    `rejectionReason` and the changes[] for the rejected diff.\n446\t  - **Secret redaction**: a payload stuffed with a JWT, postgres connection\n447\t    URL, RSA `-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----` block, `Bearer …` header, and\n448\t    `cf-access-jwt-assertion: …` line is fully redacted to\n449\t    `PEEK_AUDIT_REDACTED` before persistence; the serialized stored payload\n450\t    contains none of the raw secret strings.\n451\t  - **Empty actorEmail**: returns `{ ok: false, reason: \"invalid_payload\" }`\n452\t    and writes nothing to the SQL mock (no insert call, no `sql.json` call).\n453\t  - **Insert failure**: a rejected insert returns `{ ok: false, reason:\n454\t    \"insert_failed\" }`, the injected logger is invoked with\n455\t    `\"[peek-audit] insert failed\"` + `{ eventType }`.\n456\t  - **Error containment**: even when the underlying DB error string contains\n457\t    `password=hunter2`, the structured result never contains those bytes —\n458\t    the writer's return type is a closed union with no error detail.\n459\t- The test creates a typed SQL mock that captures both the tagged-template\n460\t  call (strings + values) and `sql.json(...)` invocations so the writer's\n461\t  payload-shaping contract is asserted directly without touching live\n462\t  Postgres. The mock is passed via the writer's `options.sql` injection\n463\t  seam (the same seam used in production calls when iterations need to run\n464\t  inside a transaction).\n465\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n466\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (115/115 — was 106/106, +9 new).\n467\t\n468\t\n469\t## Iteration 12 — 2026-04-25T11:13:59Z — OK\n470\t- **Log**: iteration-012.log\n471\t\n472\t\n473\t## Iteration 13 — 2026-04-25\n474\t\n475\t- Added the FR-3/FR-10 command-center attention queue query module so the\n476\t  command-center page can render exception states without per-page hardcoded\n477\t  thresholds:\n478\t  - `peek/src/server/db/queries/get-command-center-attention.ts` —\n479\t    `getCommandCenterAttention(options?)` runs seven bounded count queries in\n480\t    parallel and returns a `PeekCommandCenterAttention` envelope:\n481\t    1. `failed_claims` — `referral_claims.status IN ('failed', 'error')`,\n482\t       drill-down `/growth/referrals?claimStatus=failed`.\n483\t    2. `dead_queue_events` — `event_queue.status = 'dead'`, drill-down\n484\t       `/operations/queue?status=dead`.\n485\t    3. `stuck_rounds_flipyou_potshot` — `rounds` in nonterminal phases\n486\t       (`'created' | 'locked' | 'settling'`) older than the age threshold OR\n487\t       `settle_attempts > max`, drill-down `/games?stuck=true`.\n488\t    4. `stuck_rounds_closecall` — `closecall_rounds.phase = 'open'` older than\n489\t       the age threshold (Pyth settles on minute boundaries), drill-down\n490\t       `/games/closecall?stuck=true`.\n491\t    5. `pending_sol_crate_payouts` — `crate_drops.crate_type = 'sol' AND\n492\t       status = 'pending'`, drill-down\n493\t       `/economy/rewards?crateType=sol&status=pending`.\n494\t    6. `stale_active_dogpile_events` — `dogpile_events.status = 'active' AND\n495\t       ends_at < now()` (should have transitioned to `'ended'`), drill-down\n496\t       `/operations/dogpile?status=active`.\n497\t    7. `high_value_exports_24h` — `operator_events.event_type = 'peek.export'\n498\t       AND created_at > now() - 24h AND (payload->>'resultCount')::int > 1000`,\n499\t       drill-down `/audit?eventType=peek.export`.\n500\t  - Each metric is shaped as the foundational `PeekMetric` (FR-4 metric\n501\t    metadata: stable id, label, value/valueDisplay, unit, source table,\n502\t    windowLabel, asOf, definition, freshness, drilldownHref) so the\n503\t    metric-strip primitive renders it without component-side branching.\n504\t  - `COMMAND_CENTER_DEFAULTS` exposes the thresholds (5m stuck rounds, >3\n505\t    settle attempts, 24h export window, >1000-row export threshold) and the\n506\t    function accepts a `CommandCenterOptions` argument with `sql`,\n507\t    `thresholds`, and `now` overrides so future iteration tests can drive\n508\t    deterministic count + asOf assertions and so future tuning does not\n509\t    require module edits.\n510\t  - All seven queries are bounded (`select count(*)::int as \"value\"`); no\n511\t    row-level data crosses the wire from the command-center query — per-feature\n512\t    pages own their drill-down rows.\n513\t- Added `PeekCommandCenterAttention` and `PeekCommandCenterAttentionId` view\n514\t  models in `peek/src/lib/types/peek.ts` so the command-center page can import\n515\t  the typed envelope without leaking server imports.\n516\t- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n517\t  `pnpm test` ✅ (115/115, no regressions; command-center query + page tests\n518\t  land in iterations 14–15 per the checklist split).\n519\t## Iteration 13 — 2026-04-25T11:18:38Z — OK\n520\t- **Log**: iteration-013.log\n521\t\n522\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"042e06eb-8d45-46fd-a019-d381aebe19ab","uuid":"a1082928-7ec1-4ef3-b89c-91f4d64436f9","timestamp":"2026-04-25T11:19:03.749Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/305-peek-operations-admin/history.md","content":"# Implementation History — 305-peek-operations-admin\n\nIteration log for the autonomous spec loop. Each entry records what was\nattempted and whether it succeeded. The agent reads this file at the start\nof every iteration to understand prior context.\n\n---\n\n## Iteration 1 — 2026-04-25\n\n- Added `jose@6.2.2` to `peek/package.json` as a runtime dep.\n- Rewrote `peek/src/server/cloudflare-access.ts` on top of `jose`:\n  `jwtVerify` with `algorithms: ['RS256']`, `audience`, `issuer`, and\n  `currentDate`, using `createLocalJWKSet` when callers pass an in-memory\n  JWKS (test path) and `createRemoteJWKSet` against\n  `${teamDomain}/cdn-cgi/access/certs` otherwise (cached per issuer).\n- Removed all custom RSA/JWKS/base64url/JSON-claim crypto helpers; mapped\n  jose error subclasses (`JWTExpired`, `JWTClaimValidationFailed` with\n  `claim === \"iss\"`/`\"aud\"`, `JOSEAlgNotAllowed`, `JOSENotSupported`,\n  `JWKSNoMatchingKey`, `JWSSignatureVerificationFailed`,\n  `JWKSTimeout`/`JWKSInvalid`/`JWKInvalid`, `JWTInvalid`/`JWSInvalid`)\n  back onto the existing `CloudflareAccessVerificationReason` union so\n  callers and existing tests are unchanged.\n- Preserved the public surface: `verifyCloudflareAccessJwt`,\n  `getVerifiedCloudflareAccessEmailFromHeaders`, and\n  `VERIFIED_ACCESS_EMAIL_HEADER` keep their shapes; `proxy.ts` and\n  `app/layout.tsx` need no edits.\n- Targeted check: `pnpm --dir peek lint`, `pnpm --dir peek typecheck`,\n  and `pnpm --dir peek test` — all green; 21/21 unit tests pass.\n\n## Iteration 1 — 2026-04-25T09:45:06Z — BLOCKED\n- **Blocker**: No file changes detected — agent made no progress.\n- **Log**: iteration-001.log\n\n## Iteration 2 — 2026-04-25\n\n- Expanded `peek/src/server/__tests__/cloudflare-access.test.ts` for the\n  jose-backed verifier: malformed token, expired (`exp` in the past),\n  invalid issuer (signed with `https://other.cloudflareaccess.com`),\n  invalid audience, bad signature (sign with key A, present JWK B with\n  the same `kid`), `alg: \"none\"` rejection, missing email claim\n  (returns `ok: true, email: null`), and case/whitespace normalization\n  (`\"  Admin@Example.COM  \"` → `\"admin@example.com\"`).\n- Lowercased + trimmed in `normalizeEmail` so the verified email\n  identity is canonical for FR-2 role matching.\n- Replaced the implicit `NODE_ENV === \"development\"` bypass in\n  `peek/proxy.ts` with the spec-required explicit `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL`\n  bypass: dev-only, validates email shape, sets the\n  `VERIFIED_ACCESS_EMAIL_HEADER` so server context still gets a normalized\n  actor identity. Production never honors the bypass; missing CF env in\n  prod still returns 500.\n- Rewrote `peek/src/server/__tests__/cloudflare-access-middleware.test.ts`\n  with `vi.stubEnv` (TS forbids assigning to `process.env.NODE_ENV`) and\n  added: prod blocks without JWT (existing), prod 500 on missing CF env,\n  prod ignores `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL`, dev honors `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL`\n  with case normalization, dev rejects malformed `PEEK_DEV_ACCESS_EMAIL`.\n- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n  `pnpm test` ✅ (31/31, +10 new).\n\n## Iteration 2 — 2026-04-25T10:32:41Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-002.log\n\n## Iteration 3 — 2026-04-25\n\n- Added `peek/src/server/access-policy.ts`:\n  - `PeekRole = \"business\" | \"admin\"`, `PeekRolePolicyEntry = { match, role }`\n    where `match` is either an exact email (`alice@example.com`) or a wildcard\n    domain (`*@example.com`).\n  - `parsePeekRolePolicy(raw)` validates entries: trims/lowercases, drops\n    invalid `role` values, drops missing/non-string `match` values, validates\n    wildcard domain shape, and de-duplicates exact `(match, role)` pairs.\n  - `loadPeekRolePolicyFromEnv()` reads `PEEK_ACCESS_POLICY` JSON; returns\n    `[]` on missing/malformed input (fail-closed for env-driven config).\n  - `normalizeActorEmail()` and `resolveRoleForEmail()` implement\n    case-insensitive matching and admin precedence: any matching `admin`\n    rule wins (short-circuit), otherwise first matching `business` wins.\n  - `getPeekActorContext()` reads `next/headers` for the trusted\n    `VERIFIED_ACCESS_EMAIL_HEADER` (set only by the proxy), normalizes it,\n    resolves the role, and returns `{ email, role }` or `null`. Browser\n    headers are never trusted — the policy is loaded from server env only.\n- Hardened `peek/proxy.ts`: clones `request.headers` and unconditionally\n  `delete()`s `VERIFIED_ACCESS_EMAIL_HEADER` at the top of every code path,\n  so a spoofed `x-peek-verified-access-email` header from the browser cannot\n  survive into server context — even on the dev no-config and dev no-bypass\n  branches. The header is only ever (re-)set with the dev-bypass email or a\n  jose-verified Cloudflare Access email.\n- Targeted check (peek): `pnpm lint` ✅, `pnpm typecheck` ✅,\n  `pnpm test` ✅ (31/31, no regressions; access-policy unit tests land in\n  the next iteration per the checklist split).\n\n## Iteration 3 — 2026-04-25T10:36:33Z — OK\n- **Log**: iteration-003.log\n\n## Iteration 4 — 2026-04-25\n\n- Extended `peek/src/server/access-policy.ts` with the FR-2 centralized\n  route-prefix and action-id authorization helpers:\n  - `PEEK_ROUTE_RULES` table (`/audit` → `admin`); other routes fall back to\n    `PEEK_DEFAULT_ROUTE_ROLES = [\"business\", \"admin\"]` per System Invariant\n    #6 (read-only default for any resolved peek role).\n  - `PEEK_ACTION_RULES` table covering the FR-14 initial mutation candidates:\n    `kol_rate.update` (`business`/`admin`), `fraud_flag.status.update`\n    (`admin`), `dogpile.cancel` (`admin`), `reward_config.update` (`admin`).\n  - `getRequiredRolesForRoute(path)` normalizes the path (strips query/hash,\n    trailing slash) and resolves the most-specific matching prefix; unknown\n    paths return the documented default.\n  - `isRouteAllowedForRole(path, role)` → false for `null` role, otherwise\n    membership in the resolved required-roles list.\n  - `getRequiredRolesForAction(actionId)` returns the required roles or\n    `null` when the action id is unknown; `isActionAllowedForRole` fails\n    c